HEADWORD: Uniseptate
<hw>U`ni*sep"tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Uni-</ets>
+ <ets>septate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having but one
septum, or partition; -- said of two-celled fruits, such as the silicles
of cruciferous plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uniserial</ent>⟦br⟧
